Credit Card Approval Prediction System
📌 Project Overview

The Credit Card Approval Prediction System is a Machine Learning and Data Management project designed to analyze applicant information and predict whether a credit card application should be approved or rejected.

The project uses applicant demographic details, employment information, financial history, and previous credit records to identify patterns that influence credit card approval decisions. The Entity Relationship Diagram (ERD) provides the database structure required to store and manage all relevant information efficiently.

🎯 Project Objectives
Predict credit card approval outcomes using machine learning algorithms.
Analyze applicant financial and demographic profiles.
Identify factors that influence approval or rejection decisions.
Maintain historical records for future risk assessment.
Support credit risk management and decision-making processes.
🏗️ Database Design

The database is designed using seven main entities:

1. Applicant

Stores personal, demographic, and financial information of applicants.

Attributes:

Applicant_ID (Primary Key)
Gender
Date_of_Birth
Marital_Status
Number_of_Dependents
Education_Level
Occupation_Type
Income_Type
Annual_Income
Employment_Duration
Housing_Type
Phone_Number
Email
Current_Address
Status
2. Application

Stores information related to credit card applications submitted by applicants.

Attributes:

Application_ID (Primary Key)
Applicant_ID (Foreign Key)
Application_Date
Requested_Credit_Limit
Purpose
Application_Status
Approval_Date
3. Credit Decision

Contains the final decision regarding an application.

Attributes:

Decision_ID (Primary Key)
Application_ID (Foreign Key)
Decision_Date
Approval_Status
Reason_Code
Risk_Score
4. Credit Card

Stores approved credit card information.

Attributes:

Card_ID (Primary Key)
Application_ID (Foreign Key)
Card_Type
Credit_Limit
Interest_Rate
Issue_Date
Card_Status
5. Credit History

Maintains previous financial and borrowing records of applicants.

Attributes:

History_ID (Primary Key)
Applicant_ID (Foreign Key)
Loan_Type
Account_Type
Credit_Limit
Outstanding_Amount
Payment_History
Default_Flag
Record_Date
6. Payment History

Tracks repayment records associated with issued credit cards.

Attributes:

Payment_ID (Primary Key)
Card_ID (Foreign Key)
Payment_Date
Amount_Paid
Payment_Status
Due_Amount
7. Reference Data

Stores master/reference values used across the system.

Examples:

Income Types
Occupation Types
| Relationship                     | Cardinality |
| -------------------------------- | ----------- |
| Applicant → Application          | One-to-Many |
| Application → Credit Decision    | One-to-One  |
| Application → Credit Card        | One-to-One  |
| Credit Card → Payment History    | One-to-Many |
| Applicant → Credit History       | One-to-Many |
| Credit History → Credit Decision | Many-to-One |
| Reference Data → Other Entities  | One-to-Many |

